  "title": "Digital Marketing manager",
  "description": "<p><u><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></u></p><p>- Develop, implement, and manage digital marketing strategies\nacross all digital channels</p><p>- Plan and execute campaigns including Google Ads, Meta\n(Facebook/Instagram), LinkedIn, SEO, and email marketing</p><p>- Manage social media accounts and content strategy</p><p>- Optimize website and landing pages for conversion and SEO</p><p>- Monitor, analyze, and report on performance using tools like\nGoogle Analytics</p><p>- Manage marketing budget and ensure maximum ROI</p><p>- Coordinate with designers, content creators, and external\nagencies</p><p>- Identify new trends, tools, and opportunities in digital\nmarketing</p><p>- Build and manage the company’s online brand presence</p><p>- Able to create and manage AI agents is a plus point</p><p><u><strong>Requirements & Qualifications</strong></u></p><p>- Minimum Diploma in Marketing, Business, Computer Science or\nrelated field</p><p>- 5+ years of experience in marketing</p><p>- Experience with analytics tools (Google Analytics, Search\nConsole, etc.)</p><p>- Good English and Computer skills</p><p><u><strong>Other Information:</strong></u></p><p>- 5 workdays a week</p><p>- Able to work in weekends, shift and public holidays</p>",
